Review_Text: I enjoyed this movie to a certain extent, I feel as though a film like this could seem very authentic and genuine but it gave me the opposite feeling. Throughout almost the entire film I was bored and felt like it as watching a lot of people attempt to make something feel authentic with recreating things that happened before that. Now with that out of the way I can get to the good things about this film, i think it took on a very "up for debate" part of society and showed both sides fairly and without bias, it is also somewhat educational and I feel as though i saw many people and many people families. All in al l 6/10.
